100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 19, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing disarmament in the wake of World War I and seeking to stabilize international tensions. In the United States, President Calvin Coolidge continued to advocate for economic prosperity and a reduction in government intervention. Meanwhile, in Japan, the government unveiled plans to strengthen its military presence in response to growing regional threats.
